  "bio": "One of the IPL's most widely-travelled head coaches, with two distinct stints at Rajasthan Royals (2013-2015, 2018-2019) sandwiching a spell at Delhi Daredevils (2016-2017). Replaced Monty Desai at RR for 2013 and immediately took the side to the Qualifier 2 playoffs, including a franchise-record 13 straight home wins. Returned to RR in 2018 after their 2016-17 suspension ended, taking them back to the Eliminator playoffs. Previously best known as mental conditioning coach of the 2011 ODI World Cup winning India side under Gary Kirsten.",
